{"key":"processedPost-8762120","value":{"id":8762120,"first":8761989,"last":8775620,"when":1218556873,"utime":"08/12/08 07:01 PM","content":"Both of those bags of lime say they supply magnesium, so don't use either one.&nbsp; Look for hydrated garden lime. If either of those lime bags give the percent of Mg, make sure it's not over 2%.<br />The gypsum will be fine, but you'll want to smash the pellets into a powder before using.<br />The coir is a great substrate material.&nbsp; It isn't a 'coir or peat' question because they have different functions.&nbsp; Use coir for the substrate, with gypsum and maybe some of your spent coffee grinds tossed in, but no lime.&nbsp; Use peat moss and vermiculite, with gypsum and lime for the casing layer.<br />RR","title":"Re: Are these the correct products for casing...?"}}